cs.LG, cs.CR, cs.SY, cs.AI, cs.NE 

The paper discusses the use of machine learning algorithms for attack detection in the smart grid. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also deals with security issues in the smart grid, which suggests the category cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The use of statistical and geometric properties of attack vectors suggests the category cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper also discusses the use of decision- and feature-level fusion, which suggests the category cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the use of supervised and semi-supervised learning algorithms suggests the category cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
